Limamin cocin Ingila wanda ya lashe Victoria Cross a lokacin yakin duniya na farko a matsayin mayaƙa an yi bikin a garinsu shekaru 100 bayan haka.
Lt. Reverend Bernard Vann ya lashe kyautar a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918 a cikin harin a Bellenglise da Lehaucourt.
Duk da haka, an kashe shi da wani maharbi kwanaki hudu bayan haka kuma bai san cewa ya lashe lambar yabo ta soja ta Birtaniya ba.
A ranar Asabar an bayyana wani dutse na tunawa da jikokinsa biyu a Rushden, Northamptonshire.
Ɗaya daga cikin jikokinsa, Michael Vann, ya ce "abin da ke da alamar alama" ne cewa dutsen ya bayyana daidai shekaru 100 bayan nasarar kyautar kakansa.
A cewar London Gazette, a ranar 29 ga Satumba, 1918, Lt. Kur ya jagoranci rundunarsa a fadin Canal de Saint-Quentin "a cikin ƙura da wuta daga bindigogi da bindigogi".
Daga baya ya yi sauri zuwa layin wuta kuma tare da babban ƙarfin hali ya jagoranci layin gaba kafin ya tafi harbi a kan wurin shi kadai kuma ya rasa hankalin uku daga cikin tawagar.
